{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":38010,"duration_api_ms":37989,"num_turns":2,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a4175762-e5c0-4038-b5bd-d5151eac7c00","total_cost_usd":0.26992299999999997,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":34330,"cache_read_input_tokens":32741,"output_tokens":1559,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":34330,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":3,"outputTokens":1559,"cacheReadInputTokens":32741,"cacheCreationInputTokens":34330,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.26992299999999997,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"rulings":[{"amendment_id":"fr-8-5aba0f56","decision":"reject","rationale":"The dissenting reviewer (reviewer 2) provides the most technically precise counter-argument: ManagedChild::wait() uses try_wait() polling to check child exit status, not a blocking wait that depends on pipe closure. This undermines the core premise of the amendment — that open pipe read-ends could cause the background reap task to hang in wait(). On Unix, waitpid() (underlying process wait) returns when the child changes state (exits after SIGKILL), regardless of whether pipe handles are still open. Since SIGKILL is sent via force_kill() before wait() is called, the child will be terminated and wait() will observe the exit promptly via try_wait() polling. The amendment's causal chain (open pipes → wait() hangs) does not hold given the actual wait implementation. While explicitly dropping pipe handles before spawning the reap task would be tidy defensive code, accepting an amendment whose technical premise is incorrect is not warranted. The 2-1 accept split reflects genuine uncertainty, but the rejecting reviewer's specific mechanism-level rebuttal is more persuasive than the accepting reviewers' acknowledgment that the window is 'extremely narrow' on Linux — narrow because the described hang doesn't actually occur, not because it's merely unlikely."}],"summary":"Rejected the single disputed amendment fr-8-5aba0f56. The amendment claims a race where open pipe handles could cause the background reap task's wait() to hang after timeout fires. The dissenting reviewer's technical counter-argument is decisive: ManagedChild::wait() polls via try_wait() checking process exit status, which does not block on pipe closure. Since force_kill() sends SIGKILL before wait() is invoked, the child exits promptly and try_wait() observes it regardless of pipe handle state. The amendment's causal mechanism is not substantiated by the actual implementation."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"cda643a9-546d-4866-96fc-ffa8de760ab9"}
